'''Ali Yousif Hashim Najatee''' ({{langx|ar|علي يوسف هاشم}}; born 19 January 1996) is an Iraqi professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a forward for [[Al-Talaba]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

Coming up through the youth ranks at [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]], Yousif broke into the first team in 2014, aged 18, and spent his early career with the Iraqi giants, spending the [[2016-17 Iraqi Premier League|2016-17]] season out on loan at [[Naft Al-Wasat SC|Naft Al-Wasat]] and [[Baghdad FC]] before returning to his parent club and establishing himself as a key player for them, winning the [[AFC Cup]] twice with the falcons, in 2017 and 2018. In 2019, he signed for defending champions [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]], allowing Yousif to play in the [[AFC Champions League]] for the first time in his career. He won his first trophy with Al-Shorta soon after joining, winning the [[2019 Super Cup]].

==Club career==
===Al-Shorta===
In the summer of 2019, Ali signed for defending [[Iraqi Premier League]] champions [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://alrray.org/archives/389769|title=رسميا .. الشرطة يتعاقد مع اللاعب علي يوسف
|date=10 August 2019|publisher=PONA|language=Arabic|accessdate=7 December 2021}}</ref> coming in as the replacement for former star and fan favourite [[Mohanad Ali]], who had left to join Qatari side [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]] for a rumoured $1.2 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=معلومة مؤكدة : ادارة الشرطة لن توافق على اي عرض للاعب مهند علي من اي ناد مهما كان اسمه الا في حالة حصولها على مبلغ 2 مليون دولار قيمة شراء البطاقة الدولية |url=https://twitter.com/ali_sport813/status/1146915461776445443|publisher=علي نوري|language=ar|date=4 July 2019}}</ref> In February during Al-Shorta’s Premier League match against [[Al-Kahrabaa FC|Al-Kahrabaa]], Yousif suffered a bad injury which would end his season and keep him out for no less than 6 months.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.shafaaq.com/ar/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%80%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%A7%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%BA%D8%A9-%D9%84%D9%85%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%B7%D9%88%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A7-%D8%B9%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8/|title=اصابة بليغة لمهاجم الشرطة تبعده طويلاً عن الملاعب|date=24 February 2020|publisher=Shafaaq|language=Arabic|accessdate=7 December 2021|archive-date=26 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626130322/https://www.shafaaq.com/ar/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%80%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%A7%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%BA%D8%A9-%D9%84%D9%85%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%B7%D9%88%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A7-%D8%B9%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==International career==
===Iraq===
Yousif received his first international call-up as part of [[Iraq national football team|Iraq’s]] [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup]] squad. He made his debut for Iraq in their final group match against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]], coming off the bench.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/arabcup/arabcup2021/match-center/400175809|title=ArabCup|date=6 December 2021|publisher=FIFA|language=English|accessdate=7 December 2021}}</ref>

